Package it.apice.sapere.api.lsas.values

This package contains the definition of property values supported types.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
BooleanValue Interface that represents a boolean value that can be associated to a property.
DateTimeValue Interface that represents a datetime value that can be associated to a property.
DoubleValue Interface that represents a double value that can be associated to a property.
FloatValue Interface that represents a float value that can be associated to a property.
IntegerValue Interface that represents an integer value that can be associated to a property.
LiteralValue Interface that represents a String (literal) value that can be associated to a property.
LongValue Interface that represents a long value that can be associated to a property.
LSAidValue Interface that represents an LSA-id value that can be associated to a property.
PropertyValue<Type extends Comparable<Type>,CompType> A Property Value is a generic value (URI or Literal) that can be associated to a Property.
SDescValue Interface that represents a Semantic Description value that can be associated to a property.
URIValue THIS CLASS HAS BEEN CREATED DESPITE THE SAPERE MODEL, BECAUSE HANDLING RDF A URI DATA TYPE COULD BE USEFUL.
